  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the Identification and Protection of Victims of Trafficking among Refugees in Rwanda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will contribute to increasing trafficking in persons (TIP) awareness, identification, and referrals among the refugee community in Rwanda and staff operating in refugee settings, including in the six camps and their surrounding communities.  This project proposes to meet this objective through sensitization activities for increased awareness among refugee communities of the issues of trafficking and improved services offered by the authorities. Throughout the project, the One UN partners will also seek to strengthen such mechanisms for refugee populations that are increasingly at risk of TIP.</narrative>
  </description>
